          "boundElements": null,
          "updated": 1769242824887,
          "link": null,
          "locked": false,
          "text": "Cons : - \n\n    1. Not possible to do synchronous task. \n    2. Higher Latency campared to sync API calls \n           What does latency means here the amount time between adding task\n            to the queue and the task actually getting processed by consumer \n    3. Need additional Infra \n    4. Higher Network Overhead\n\nMost Common Message Queues \n    \n1. Apache Kafka\n2. Rabbit MQ\n3. Amazon SQS\n\n\n\n\n      \n\n    ",
          "fontSize": 16,
          "fontFamily": 8,
          "textAlign": "left",
          "verticalAlign": "top",
          "containerId": null,
          "originalText": "Cons : - \n\n    1. Not possible to do synchronous task. \n    2. Higher Latency campared to sync API calls \n           What does latency means here the amount time between adding task\n            to the queue and the task actually getting processed by consumer \n    3. Need additional Infra \n    4. Higher Network Overhead\n\nMost Common Message Queues \n    \n1. Apache Kafka\n2. Rabbit MQ\n3. Amazon SQS\n\n\n\n\n      \n\n    ",
          "autoResize": true,
          "lineHeight": 1.25
        },
        {
          "id": "H6BLmp3bVw0MKaijpCVjk",
          "type": "text",
          "x": 3922.4269035471334,
          "y": -7486.664692803934,
          "width": 791.9989013671875,
          "height": 320,
          "angle": 0,
          "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
          "backgroundColor": "transparent",
          "fillStyle": "solid",
          "strokeWidth": 4,
          "strokeStyle": "solid",
          "roughness": 0,
          "opacity": 100,
          "groupIds": [],
          "frameId": null,
          "index": "b3T",
          "roundness": null,
          "seed": 1567898120,
          "version": 1217,
          "versionNonce": 550647304,
          "isDeleted": false,
          "boundElements": null,
          "updated": 1769243345598,
          "link": null,
          "locked": false,
          "text": "Apache Kafka : \n\n    1. Open Source: Build By linkedIn, now part of Apache\n    2. High Throughput: A cluster Can handle up to 10Mil msg/s (trillion/day)\n    3. Ultra Low Latency(Overhead) : claims < 2ms latency from message insertion to\n       consumption (provide that queue is empty) \n    4. Horizontal Scalability : Automatically manages Partitions across mutiple server\n        1000s of brokers(servers), 100,000s of partitions petabytes of data\n    5. Fault Tolerant : Automatically Replicates Messages across Mutiple Servers, \n        and it stores the messages on disk\n    6. High Availablity: Can deploy clusters across availability zones.\n    7. Persistent: Saves the messages on disk to ensure they are not lost. \n        Multiple consumers groups can consume the same message. \n    8. Messages Ordering: Provides Strict message ordering ( within each parititons only) \n    9. Batted Tested: Used By all Large Companies and tens of thousands of other companies\n ",
          "fontSize": 16,
          "fontFamily": 8,
          "textAlign": "left",
          "verticalAlign": "top",
          "containerId": null,
          "originalText": "Apache Kafka : \n\n    1. Open Source: Build By linkedIn, now part of Apache\n    2. High Throughput: A cluster Can handle up to 10Mil msg/s (trillion/day)\n    3. Ultra Low Latency(Overhead) : claims < 2ms latency from message insertion to\n       consumption (provide that queue is empty) \n    4. Horizontal Scalability : Automatically manages Partitions across mutiple server\n        1000s of brokers(servers), 100,000s of partitions petabytes of data\n    5. Fault Tolerant : Automatically Replicates Messages across Mutiple Servers, \n        and it stores the messages on disk\n    6. High Availablity: Can deploy clusters across availability zones.\n    7. Persistent: Saves the messages on disk to ensure they are not lost. \n        Multiple consumers groups can consume the same message. \n    8. Messages Ordering: Provides Strict message ordering ( within each parititons only) \n    9. Batted Tested: Used By all Large Companies and tens of thousands of other companies\n ",
          "autoResize": true,
          "lineHeight": 1.25
        },
        {
          "id": "dxoWzPPawij6lOXy8zlwi",
          "type": "text",
          "x": 3947.999532098476,
          "y": -7159.164815462586,
          "width": 721.5989990234375,
          "height": 440,
          "angle": 0,
          "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
          "backgroundColor": "transparent",
          "fillStyle": "solid",
          "strokeWidth": 4,
          "strokeStyle": "solid",
          "roughness": 0,
          "opacity": 100,
          "groupIds": [],
          "frameId": null,
          "index": "b3U",
