          "versionNonce": 1416874360,
          "isDeleted": false,
          "boundElements": null,
          "updated": 1769245125566,
          "link": null,
          "locked": false,
          "text": "Producers And Consumers\n\nProducers are Applications that publish(write) event to kafka\nConsumers subscribe to (read and Process) these events\n\n\nThey Both are fully decoupled and Agnostic of each other\n   producers never need to wait for consumers\n\n\nConsumers Groups(Scalability)\n    1. A single consumer might not be able to process all the messages(10M/s) \n    2. We might need multiple Types of comsumers that wish to consume the messages\n    \n\nSolution: \n\n    Consumers must provide a group.id when they join\n    Kafka Assigns a special coordinator to manage each consumer group\n        consumer group send heartbeats to the coordinator to remain alive\n\n ",
          "fontSize": 16,
          "fontFamily": 8,
          "textAlign": "left",
          "verticalAlign": "top",
          "containerId": null,
          "originalText": "Producers And Consumers\n\nProducers are Applications that publish(write) event to kafka\nConsumers subscribe to (read and Process) these events\n\n\nThey Both are fully decoupled and Agnostic of each other\n   producers never need to wait for consumers\n\n\nConsumers Groups(Scalability)\n    1. A single consumer might not be able to process all the messages(10M/s) \n    2. We might need multiple Types of comsumers that wish to consume the messages\n    \n\nSolution: \n\n    Consumers must provide a group.id when they join\n    Kafka Assigns a special coordinator to manage each consumer group\n        consumer group send heartbeats to the coordinator to remain alive\n\n ",
          "autoResize": true,
          "lineHeight": 1.25
        },
