          "text": "Consumer-Partition Mapping & Consumer Offsets\n\nEach partition of a topic is consumed by exactly 1 consumer within each comsumer group\nFor every such(partition, consumer) pair , kafka maintains an integer offset that specifies which message in\nthe partition should the consumer read next\nconsumer offser are maintained in a special topic named __consumer_offsets\n\nThis mapping b/w consumers and partitions is maintained by the coordinator \n\n      \n    Can the same partitions be assigned to multiple consumers ? \n\n        Multiple Consumers within the same consumer group ? No\n        Multiple Consumers each in a diff consumer group : Yes\n    \n         ",
