          "text": "Can Mutiple partitions be assinged to the same consumers group? \n Yes\n\nEach Partition of topic is consumed by exactly 1 consumer within each group that subscribes to that topic\n\n:: we must always ensume that \n    #partitions >= consumers \n\nRebalancing: If a consumer joins or leaves, kafka redistrubutes the partitions among the group's consumers.\n\nFor example, if we're creating a new kafka topic called imageUploads we try to guess the max number of \nconsumers we might need in the future that consumer from this topix, and set the number of partitions higher than that\n\n",
